==English==
===Etymology===
From [[w:Irish language|Irish]][[Category:Irish derivations]] naigín, or [[w:Gaelic language|Gaelic]][[Category:Gaelic derivations]] noigean. Compare with [[nog]].

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒɡɪn|-ɒɡɪn]]

===Noun===
'''noggin'''

#A [[small]] [[mug]] or [[cup]]. 
#''(Obsolete or colloquial)'' A measure equivalent to a gill.
#{{slang}} The [[head]].  

(On the semantic development from "cup" to "head" see also the etymologies of German ''[[Kopf]]'' and French ''[[tête]]''.)

also possibly linked to the phrase "naggan of vodka"(a small bottle of vodka).

